text.section:
When the Parole Board orders restitution, the board shall:
Order the restitution to be paid to a specific person or organization through the Division of Probation and Parole, which shall disburse the moneys as ordered by the board;
Set the amount of restitution to be paid, if not already set;
Set the amount and frequency of each restitution payment or require the payment to be made in a lump sum.

When the Parole Board orders restitution, the Department of Probation and Parole shall:
Monitor and oversee the collection of the restitution;
Institute parole violation proceedings if the restitution is not being paid;
Institute sanctions against the defendant if restitution is not being paid and good cause is not shown for the nonpayment; and
Maintain parole supervision over the defendant until restitution has been paid in full.
